                                <body xml:id="ch1.sc3.0097">                                                
                                                  <p><name type="person" key="376"><hi
                                                  rend="initialcap">B</hi>ROWN, <hi
                                                  rend="initialcap">P</hi>RESLEY <hi
                                                  rend="initialcap">I</hi>.</name>, Corporal, <name
                                                  type="organization" key="340">Co. B, 102d
                                                  Pennsylvania Volunteers</name>, aged 24 years,
                                                                  received, at the battle of <name type="BATTLE" key="259">the Wilderness, Virginia</name>, <date
                                                  type="injury" when="1864-05-06">May 6th,
                                                  1864</date>, a gunshot wound of scalp, a conoidal
                                                  ball entering at middle of left parietal bone,
                                                  passing backwards, making a flesh wound two inches
                                                  in length, denuding the bone.  He was admitted to
                                                  <name type="hospital" key="176">Lincoln
                                                  Hospital</name>, Washington, D. C., on <date
                                                  type="admit" when="1864-05-11">May 11th</date>,
                                                  and, on <date type="transfer" when="1864-05-16">May 16th</date>, was transferred to <name type="hospital">Patterson
                                                                  Park Hospital, Baltimore</name>, Maryland; thence, on
                                                  <date type="transfer" when="18464-05-21">May
                                                                  21st</date>, to hospital at <name type="place">York, Pennsylvania</name>.  <name type="person">Acting Assistant Surgeon H. S. Smyser</name>, under whose
                                                  care the patient came at the latter hospital,
                                                  reports that the patient stated that there was
                                                  loss of sensation in right arm and hand from the
                                                  moment he was struck by the ball. On June 10th,
                                                  the arm was recovering, and, on <date
                                                  type="transfer" when="1864-06-13">June
                                                  13th</date>, the patient was transferred to the
                                                                  hospital at <name type="place">Pittsburg, Pennsylvania</name>, whence he was
                                                  returned to duty on <date type="duty"
                                                  when="1865-05-09">May 9th, 1865</date>. </p>                                                
